{
  "video_id": "LZXUR4z2P9w",
  "title": "How fear of nuclear power is hurting the environment | Michael Shellenberger",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12825.0,
      "end_time": 14488.0,
      "text": "Have you heard the news?"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 14488.0,
      "end_time": 17462.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re in a clean energy revolution."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 17462.0,
      "end_time": 19476.0,
      "text": "And where I live in Berkeley, California,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 19476.0,
      "end_time": 23784.0,
      "text": "it seems like every day I see a new roof with new solar panels going up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 23784.0,
      "end_time": 25812.0,
      "text": "electric car in the driveway."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 25812.0,
      "end_time": 29051.0,
      "text": "Germany sometimes gets half its power from solar,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 29051.0,
      "end_time": 33568.0,
      "text": "and India is now committed to building 10 times more solar"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 33568.0,
      "end_time": 34920.0,
      "text": "than we have in California,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 34920.0,
      "end_time": 36896.0,
      "text": "by the year 2022."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 36896.0,
      "end_time": 39874.0,
      "text": "Even nuclear seems to be making a comeback."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 39874.0,
      "end_time": 42943.0,
      "text": "Bill Gates is in China working with engineers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 42943.0,
      "end_time": 45764.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s 40 different companies that are working together"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 45764.0,
      "end_time": 49113.0,
      "text": "to try to race to build the first reactor that runs on waste,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 49113.0,
      "end_time": 50374.0,
      "text": "that can&#39;t melt down"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 50374.0,
      "end_time": 52492.0,
      "text": "and is cheaper than coal."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 52492.0,
      "end_time": 55430.0,
      "text": "And so you might start to ask:"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 55430.0,
      "end_time": 57251.0,
      "text": "Is this whole global warming problem"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 57251.0,
      "end_time": 60504.0,
      "text": "going to be a lot easier to solve than anybody imagined?"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 60504.0,
      "end_time": 62479.0,
      "text": "That was the question we wanted to know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 62479.0,
      "end_time": 65745.0,
      "text": "so my colleagues and I decided to take a deep dive into the data."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 65745.0,
      "end_time": 67796.0,
      "text": "We were a little skeptical of some parts"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 67796.0,
      "end_time": 69827.0,
      "text": "of the clean energy revolution story,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 69827.0,
      "end_time": 72611.0,
      "text": "but what we found really surprised us."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 72611.0,
      "end_time": 76545.0,
      "text": "The first thing is that clean energy has been increasing."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 76545.0,
      "end_time": 81023.0,
      "text": "This is electricity from clean energy sources over the last 20 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 81023.0,
      "end_time": 84765.0,
      "text": "But when you look at the percentage of global electricity"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 84765.0,
      "end_time": 86128.0,
      "text": "from clean energy sources,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 86128.0,
      "end_time": 90718.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s actually been in decline from 36 percent to 31 percent."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 90718.0,
      "end_time": 92924.0,
      "text": "And if you care about climate change,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 92924.0,
      "end_time": 95094.0,
      "text": "you&#39;ve got to go in the opposite direction"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 95094.0,
      "end_time": 98668.0,
      "text": "to 100 percent of our electricity from clean energy sources,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 98668.0,
      "end_time": 100290.0,
      "text": "as quickly as possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 100290.0,
      "end_time": 101471.0,
      "text": "Now, you might wonder,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 101471.0,
      "end_time": 105364.0,
      "text": "&quot;Come on, how much could five percentage points of global electricity be?&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 105364.0,
      "end_time": 107155.0,
      "text": "Well, it turns out to be quite a bit."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 107155.0,
      "end_time": 110322.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s the equivalent of 60 nuclear plants"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 110322.0,
      "end_time": 113957.0,
      "text": "the size of Diablo Canyon, California&#39;s last nuclear plant,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 113957.0,
      "end_time": 117650.0,
      "text": "or 900 solar farms the size of Topaz,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 117650.0,
      "end_time": 120203.0,
      "text": "which is one of the biggest solar farms in the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 120203.0,
      "end_time": 123587.0,
      "text": "and certainly our biggest in California."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 123587.0,
      "end_time": 126855.0,
      "text": "A big part of this is simply that fossil fuels are increasing"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 126855.0,
      "end_time": 128132.0,
      "text": "faster than clean energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 128132.0,
      "end_time": 129395.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s understandable."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 129395.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131134.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s just a lot of poor countries"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 131134.0,
      "end_time": 133611.0,
      "text": "that are still using wood and dung and charcoal"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 133611.0,
      "end_time": 135220.0,
      "text": "as their main source of energy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 135220.0,
      "end_time": 136695.0,
      "text": "and they need modern fuels."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 136695.0,
      "end_time": 138668.0,
      "text": "But there&#39;s something else going on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 138668.0,
      "end_time": 142747.0,
      "text": "which is that one of those clean energy sources in particular"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 142747.0,
      "end_time": 146179.0,
      "text": "has actually been on the decline in absolute terms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 146179.0,
      "end_time": 147704.0,
      "text": "not just relatively."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 147704.0,
      "end_time": 148942.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s nuclear."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 148942.0,
      "end_time": 152615.0,
      "text": "You can see its generation has declined seven percent"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 152615.0,
      "end_time": 154476.0,
      "text": "over the last 10 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 154476.0,
      "end_time": 157108.0,
      "text": "Now, solar and wind have been making huge strides,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 157108.0,
      "end_time": 160040.0,
      "text": "so you hear a lot of talk about how it doesn&#39;t really matter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 160040.0,
      "end_time": 162802.0,
      "text": "because solar and wind is going to make up the difference."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 162802.0,
      "end_time": 164682.0,
      "text": "But the data says something different."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 164682.0,
      "end_time": 167751.0,
      "text": "When you combine all the electricity from solar and wind,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 167751.0,
      "end_time": 173758.0,
      "text": "you see it actually barely makes up half of the decline from nuclear."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 173758.0,
      "end_time": 176100.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s take a closer look in the United States."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 176100.0,
      "end_time": 179915.0,
      "text": "Over the last couple of years -- really 2013, 2014 --"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 179915.0,
      "end_time": 183408.0,
      "text": "we prematurely retired four nuclear power plants."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 183408.0,
      "end_time": 186231.0,
      "text": "They were almost entirely replaced with fossil fuels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 186231.0,
      "end_time": 189761.0,
      "text": "and so the consequence was that we wiped out"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 189761.0,
      "end_time": 194711.0,
      "text": "almost as much clean energy electricity that we get from solar."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 194711.0,
      "end_time": 198113.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s not unique to us."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 198113.0,
      "end_time": 201208.0,
      "text": "People think of California as a clean energy and climate leader,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 201208.0,
      "end_time": 203240.0,
      "text": "but when we looked at the data,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 203240.0,
      "end_time": 204765.0,
      "text": "what we found is that, in fact,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 204765.0,
      "end_time": 207992.0,
      "text": "California reduced emissions more slowly than the national average,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 207992.0,
      "end_time": 210359.0,
      "text": "between 2000 and 2015."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 210359.0,
      "end_time": 211618.0,
      "text": "What about Germany?"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 211618.0,
      "end_time": 213675.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re doing a lot of clean energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 213675.0,
      "end_time": 215430.0,
      "text": "But when you look at the data,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 215430.0,
      "end_time": 218732.0,
      "text": "German emissions have actually been going up since 2009,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 218732.0,
      "end_time": 221331.0,
      "text": "and there&#39;s really not anybody who&#39;s going to tell you"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 221331.0,
      "end_time": 225137.0,
      "text": "that they&#39;re going to meet their climate commitments in 2020."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 225137.0,
      "end_time": 226913.0,
      "text": "The reason isn&#39;t hard to understand."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 226913.0,
      "end_time": 230240.0,
      "text": "Solar and wind provide power about 10 to 20 percent of the time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 230240.0,
      "end_time": 232312.0,
      "text": "which means that when the sun&#39;s not shining,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 232312.0,
      "end_time": 233688.0,
      "text": "the wind&#39;s not blowing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 233688.0,
      "end_time": 235863.0,
      "text": "you still need power for your hospitals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 235863.0,
      "end_time": 238617.0,
      "text": "your homes, your cities, your factories."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 238617.0,
      "end_time": 242545.0,
      "text": "And while batteries have made some really cool improvements lately,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 242545.0,
      "end_time": 245277.0,
      "text": "the truth is, they&#39;re just never going to be as efficient"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 245277.0,
      "end_time": 246500.0,
      "text": "as the electrical grid."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 246500.0,
      "end_time": 249651.0,
      "text": "Every time you put electricity into a battery and take it out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 249651.0,
      "end_time": 253470.0,
      "text": "you lose about 20 to 40 percent of the power."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 253470.0,
      "end_time": 256087.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s why when, in California,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 256087.0,
      "end_time": 258825.0,
      "text": "we try to deal with all the solar we&#39;ve brought online --"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 258825.0,
      "end_time": 261613.0,
      "text": "we now get about 10 percent of electricity from solar --"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 261613.0,
      "end_time": 264279.0,
      "text": "when the sun goes down, and people come home from work"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 264279.0,
      "end_time": 266793.0,
      "text": "and turn on their air conditioners and their TV sets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 266793.0,
      "end_time": 268715.0,
      "text": "and every other appliance in the house,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 268715.0,
      "end_time": 271200.0,
      "text": "we need a lot of natural gas backup."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 271200.0,
      "end_time": 272389.0,
      "text": "So what we&#39;ve been doing"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 272389.0,
      "end_time": 275616.0,
      "text": "is stuffing a lot of natural gas into the side of a mountain."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 275616.0,
      "end_time": 277889.0,
      "text": "And that worked pretty well for a while,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 277889.0,
      "end_time": 280904.0,
      "text": "but then late last year, it sprung a leak."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 280904.0,
      "end_time": 282768.0,
      "text": "This is Aliso Canyon."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 282768.0,
      "end_time": 285806.0,
      "text": "So much methane gas was released,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 285806.0,
      "end_time": 289016.0,
      "text": "it was the equivalent of putting half a million cars on the road."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 289016.0,
      "end_time": 293681.0,
      "text": "It basically blew through all of our climate commitments for the year."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 293681.0,
      "end_time": 295029.0,
      "text": "Well, what about India?"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 295029.0,
      "end_time": 298304.0,
      "text": "Sometimes you have to go places to really get the right data,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 298304.0,
      "end_time": 300309.0,
      "text": "so we traveled to India a few months ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 300309.0,
      "end_time": 303464.0,
      "text": "We met with all the top officials -- solar, nuclear, the rest --"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 303464.0,
      "end_time": 305029.0,
      "text": "and what they told us is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 305029.0,
      "end_time": 307107.0,
      "text": "&quot;We&#39;re actually having more serious problems"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 307107.0,
      "end_time": 308806.0,
      "text": "than both Germany and California."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 308806.0,
      "end_time": 312363.0,
      "text": "We don&#39;t have backup; we don&#39;t have all the natural gas."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 312363.0,
      "end_time": 314919.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s just the start of it."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 314919.0,
      "end_time": 317832.0,
      "text": "Say we want to get to 100 gigawatts by 2022."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 317832.0,
      "end_time": 319808.0,
      "text": "But last year we did just five,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 319808.0,
      "end_time": 321870.0,
      "text": "and the year before that, we did five.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 321870.0,
      "end_time": 324770.0,
      "text": "So, let&#39;s just take a closer look at nuclear."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 324770.0,
      "end_time": 328017.0,
      "text": "The United Nations Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 328017.0,
      "end_time": 331012.0,
      "text": "has looked at the carbon content of all these different fuels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 331012.0,
      "end_time": 334969.0,
      "text": "and nuclear comes out really low -- it&#39;s actually lower even than solar."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 334969.0,
      "end_time": 338888.0,
      "text": "And nuclear obviously provides a lot of power --"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 338888.0,
      "end_time": 341465.0,
      "text": "24 hours a day, seven days a week."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 341465.0,
      "end_time": 345423.0,
      "text": "During a year, a single plant can provide power 92 percent of the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 345423.0,
      "end_time": 348019.0,
      "text": "What&#39;s interesting is that when you look at countries"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 348019.0,
      "end_time": 350585.0,
      "text": "that have deployed different kinds of clean energies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 350585.0,
      "end_time": 352509.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s only a few that have done so"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 352509.0,
      "end_time": 355388.0,
      "text": "at a pace consistent with dealing with the climate crisis."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 355388.0,
      "end_time": 357463.0,
      "text": "So nuclear seems like a pretty good option,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 357463.0,
      "end_time": 359525.0,
      "text": "but there&#39;s this big problem with it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 359525.0,
      "end_time": 361579.0,
      "text": "which all of you, I&#39;m sure, are aware of,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 361579.0,
      "end_time": 364431.0,
      "text": "which is that people really don&#39;t like it."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 364431.0,
      "end_time": 367646.0,
      "text": "There was a study, a survey done of people around the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 367646.0,
      "end_time": 370173.0,
      "text": "not just in the United States or Europe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 370173.0,
      "end_time": 371728.0,
      "text": "about a year and a half ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 371728.0,
      "end_time": 373086.0,
      "text": "And what they found"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 373086.0,
      "end_time": 376902.0,
      "text": "is that nuclear is actually one of the least popular forms of energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 376902.0,
      "end_time": 379356.0,
      "text": "Even oil is more popular than nuclear."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 379356.0,
      "end_time": 382546.0,
      "text": "And while nuclear kind of edges out coal, the thing is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 382546.0,
      "end_time": 386387.0,
      "text": "people don&#39;t really fear coal in the same way they fear nuclear,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 386387.0,
      "end_time": 388828.0,
      "text": "which really operates on our unconscious."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 388828.0,
      "end_time": 390487.0,
      "text": "So what is it that we fear?"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 390487.0,
      "end_time": 392061.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s really three things."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 392061.0,
      "end_time": 394325.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s the safety of the plants themselves --"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 394325.0,
      "end_time": 397154.0,
      "text": "the fears that they&#39;re going to melt down and cause damage;"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 397154.0,
      "end_time": 398523.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s the waste from them;"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 398523.0,
      "end_time": 401562.0,
      "text": "and there&#39;s the association with weapons."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 401562.0,
      "end_time": 403022.0,
      "text": "And I think, understandably,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 403022.0,
      "end_time": 407088.0,
      "text": "engineers look at those concerns and look for technological fixes."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 407088.0,
      "end_time": 410095.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s why Bill Gates is in China developing advanced reactors."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 410095.0,
      "end_time": 413243.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s why 40 different entrepreneurs are working on this problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 413243.0,
      "end_time": 415498.0,
      "text": "And I, myself, have been very excited about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 415498.0,
      "end_time": 417664.0,
      "text": "We did a report: &quot;How to Make Nuclear Cheap.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 417664.0,
      "end_time": 420586.0,
      "text": "In particular, the thorium reactor shows a lot of promise."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 420586.0,
      "end_time": 422714.0,
      "text": "So when the climate scientist, James Hansen,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 422714.0,
      "end_time": 425007.0,
      "text": "asked if I wanted to go to China with him"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 425007.0,
      "end_time": 427415.0,
      "text": "and look at the Chinese advanced nuclear program,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 427415.0,
      "end_time": 428689.0,
      "text": "I jumped at the chance."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 428689.0,
      "end_time": 431904.0,
      "text": "We were there with MIT and UC Berkeley engineers."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 431904.0,
      "end_time": 433604.0,
      "text": "And I had in my mind"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 433604.0,
      "end_time": 435940.0,
      "text": "that the Chinese would be able to do with nuclear"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 435940.0,
      "end_time": 438011.0,
      "text": "what they did with so many other things --"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 438011.0,
      "end_time": 441964.0,
      "text": "start to crank out small nuclear reactors on assembly lines,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 441964.0,
      "end_time": 446376.0,
      "text": "ship them up like iPhones or MacBooks and send them around the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 446376.0,
      "end_time": 449120.0,
      "text": "I would get one at home in Berkeley."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 449120.0,
      "end_time": 451105.0,
      "text": "But what I found was somewhat different."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 451105.0,
      "end_time": 454033.0,
      "text": "The presentations were all very exciting and very promising;"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 454033.0,
      "end_time": 456543.0,
      "text": "they have multiple reactors that they&#39;re working on."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 456543.0,
      "end_time": 459872.0,
      "text": "The time came for the thorium reactor, and a bunch of us were excited."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 459872.0,
      "end_time": 463295.0,
      "text": "They went through the whole presentation, they got to the timeline,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 463295.0,
      "end_time": 464576.0,
      "text": "and they said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 464576.0,
      "end_time": 468118.0,
      "text": "&quot;We&#39;re going to have a thorium molten salt reactor"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 468118.0,
      "end_time": 470307.0,
      "text": "ready for sale to the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 470307.0,
      "end_time": 472850.0,
      "text": "by 2040.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 472850.0,
      "end_time": 474487.0,
      "text": "And I was like, &quot;What?&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 474487.0,
      "end_time": 475526.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 475526.0,
      "end_time": 477558.0,
      "text": "I looked at my colleagues and I was like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 477558.0,
      "end_time": 479050.0,
      "text": "&quot;Excuse me --"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 479050.0,
      "end_time": 481404.0,
      "text": "can you guys speed that up a little bit?"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 481404.0,
      "end_time": 484502.0,
      "text": "Because we&#39;re in a little bit of a climate crisis right now."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 484502.0,
      "end_time": 487252.0,
      "text": "And your cities are really polluted, by the way.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 487252.0,
      "end_time": 489594.0,
      "text": "And they responded back, they were like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 489594.0,
      "end_time": 492398.0,
      "text": "&quot;I&#39;m not sure what you&#39;ve heard about our thorium program,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 492398.0,
      "end_time": 494337.0,
      "text": "but we don&#39;t have a third of our budget,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 494337.0,
      "end_time": 497473.0,
      "text": "and your department of energy hasn&#39;t been particularly forthcoming"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 497473.0,
      "end_time": 501382.0,
      "text": "with all that data you guys have on testing reactors.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 501382.0,
      "end_time": 503764.0,
      "text": "And I said, &quot;Well, I&#39;ve got an idea."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 503764.0,
      "end_time": 507384.0,
      "text": "You know how you&#39;ve got 10 years where you&#39;re demonstrating that reactor?"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 507384.0,
      "end_time": 508980.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s just skip that part,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 508980.0,
      "end_time": 511354.0,
      "text": "and let&#39;s just go right to commercializing it."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 511354.0,
      "end_time": 513379.0,
      "text": "That will save money and time.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 513379.0,
      "end_time": 515995.0,
      "text": "And the engineer just looked at me and said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 515995.0,
      "end_time": 517645.0,
      "text": "&quot;Let me ask you a question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 517645.0,
      "end_time": 521913.0,
      "text": "Would you buy a car that had never been demonstrated before?&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 521913.0,
      "end_time": 523534.0,
      "text": "So what about the other reactors?"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 523534.0,
      "end_time": 527010.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a reactor that&#39;s coming online now, they&#39;re starting to sell it."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 527010.0,
      "end_time": 528820.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a high-temperature gas reactor."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 528820.0,
      "end_time": 530845.0,
      "text": "It can&#39;t melt down."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 530845.0,
      "end_time": 533604.0,
      "text": "But it&#39;s really big and bulky, that&#39;s part of the safety,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 533604.0,
      "end_time": 535916.0,
      "text": "and nobody thinks it&#39;s going to ever get cheaper"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 535916.0,
      "end_time": 537880.0,
      "text": "than the reactors that we have."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 537880.0,
      "end_time": 541980.0,
      "text": "The ones that use waste as fuel are really cool ideas, but the truth is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 541980.0,
      "end_time": 544052.0,
      "text": "we don&#39;t actually know how to do that yet."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 544052.0,
      "end_time": 546671.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s some risk that you&#39;ll actually make more waste,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 546671.0,
      "end_time": 549489.0,
      "text": "and most people think that if you&#39;re including"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 549489.0,
      "end_time": 551595.0,
      "text": "that waste part of the process,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 551595.0,
      "end_time": 554586.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s just going to make the whole machine a lot more expensive,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 554586.0,
      "end_time": 557765.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s just adding another complicated step."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 557765.0,
      "end_time": 559695.0,
      "text": "The truth is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 559695.0,
      "end_time": 562869.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s real questions about how much of that we&#39;re going to do."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 562869.0,
      "end_time": 565779.0,
      "text": "I mean, we went to India and asked about the nuclear program."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 565779.0,
      "end_time": 568201.0,
      "text": "The government said before the Paris climate talks"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 568201.0,
      "end_time": 571281.0,
      "text": "that they were going to do something like 30 new nuclear plants."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 571281.0,
      "end_time": 573376.0,
      "text": "But when we got there and interviewed people"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 573376.0,
      "end_time": 575481.0,
      "text": "and even looked at the internal documents,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 575481.0,
      "end_time": 577957.0,
      "text": "they&#39;re now saying they&#39;re going to do about five."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 577957.0,
      "end_time": 580527.0,
      "text": "And in most of the world, especially the rich world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 580527.0,
      "end_time": 582837.0,
      "text": "they&#39;re not talking about building new reactors."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 582837.0,
      "end_time": 585149.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re actually talking about taking reactors down"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 585149.0,
      "end_time": 586839.0,
      "text": "before their lifetimes are over."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 586839.0,
      "end_time": 589651.0,
      "text": "Germany&#39;s actually pressuring its neighbors to do that."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 589651.0,
      "end_time": 591482.0,
      "text": "I mentioned the United States --"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 591482.0,
      "end_time": 595849.0,
      "text": "we could lose half of our reactors over the next 15 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 595849.0,
      "end_time": 598690.0,
      "text": "which would wipe out 40 percent of the emissions reductions"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 598690.0,
      "end_time": 601058.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re supposed to get under the Clean Power Plan."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 601058.0,
      "end_time": 604149.0,
      "text": "Of course, in Japan, they took all their nuclear plants offline,"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 604149.0,
      "end_time": 606526.0,
      "text": "replaced them with coal, natural gas, oil burning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 606526.0,
      "end_time": 610112.0,
      "text": "and they&#39;re only expected to bring online about a third to two-thirds."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 610112.0,
      "end_time": 612681.0,
      "text": "So when we went through the numbers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 612681.0,
      "end_time": 614028.0,
      "text": "and just added that up --"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 614028.0,
      "end_time": 617173.0,
      "text": "how much nuclear do we see China and India bringing online"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 617173.0,
      "end_time": 619159.0,
      "text": "over the next 15 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 619159.0,
      "end_time": 622739.0,
      "text": "how much do we see at risk of being taken offline --"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 622739.0,
      "end_time": 625052.0,
      "text": "this was the most startling finding."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 625052.0,
      "end_time": 628567.0,
      "text": "What we found is that the world is actually at risk"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 628567.0,
      "end_time": 634055.0,
      "text": "of losing four times more clean energy than we lost over the last 10 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 634055.0,
      "end_time": 637429.0,
      "text": "In other words: we&#39;re not in a clean energy revolution;"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 637429.0,
      "end_time": 640992.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re in a clean energy crisis."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 640992.0,
      "end_time": 645188.0,
      "text": "So it&#39;s understandable that engineers would look for a technical fix"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 645188.0,
      "end_time": 647166.0,
      "text": "to the fears that people have of nuclear."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 647166.0,
      "end_time": 649966.0,
      "text": "But when you consider that these are big challenges to do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 649966.0,
      "end_time": 652275.0,
      "text": "that they&#39;re going to take a long time to solve,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 652275.0,
      "end_time": 654045.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s this other issue, which is:"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 654045.0,
      "end_time": 657828.0,
      "text": "Are those technical fixes really going to solve people&#39;s fears?"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 657828.0,
      "end_time": 659410.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s take safety."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 659410.0,
      "end_time": 661919.0,
      "text": "You know, despite what people think,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 661919.0,
      "end_time": 665076.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s hard to figure out how to make nuclear power much safer."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 665076.0,
      "end_time": 667418.0,
      "text": "I mean, every medical journal that looks at it --"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 667418.0,
      "end_time": 670550.0,
      "text": "this is the most recent study from the British journal, &quot;Lancet,&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 670550.0,
      "end_time": 673027.0,
      "text": "one of the most respected journals in the world --"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 673027.0,
      "end_time": 675570.0,
      "text": "nuclear is the safest way to make reliable power."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 675570.0,
      "end_time": 677375.0,
      "text": "Everybody&#39;s scared of the accidents."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 677375.0,
      "end_time": 679693.0,
      "text": "So you go look at the accident data --"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 679693.0,
      "end_time": 681212.0,
      "text": "Fukushima, Chernobyl --"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 681212.0,
      "end_time": 683939.0,
      "text": "the World Health Organization finds the same thing:"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 683939.0,
      "end_time": 687938.0,
      "text": "the vast majority of harm is caused by people panicking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 687938.0,
      "end_time": 690282.0,
      "text": "and they&#39;re panicking because they&#39;re afraid."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 690282.0,
      "end_time": 691531.0,
      "text": "In other words,"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 691531.0,
      "end_time": 695088.0,
      "text": "the harm that&#39;s caused isn&#39;t actually caused by the machines"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 695088.0,
      "end_time": 696493.0,
      "text": "or the radiation."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 696493.0,
      "end_time": 698573.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s caused by our fears."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 698573.0,
      "end_time": 700042.0,
      "text": "And what about the waste?"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 700042.0,
      "end_time": 701658.0,
      "text": "Everyone worries about the waste."
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 701658.0,
      "end_time": 703865.0,
      "text": "Well, the interesting thing about the waste"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 703865.0,
      "end_time": 705308.0,
      "text": "is how little of it there is."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 705308.0,
      "end_time": 706709.0,
      "text": "This is just from one plant."
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 706709.0,
      "end_time": 710110.0,
      "text": "If you take all the nuclear waste we&#39;ve ever made in the United States,"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 710110.0,
      "end_time": 712333.0,
      "text": "put it on a football field, stacked it up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 712333.0,
      "end_time": 714580.0,
      "text": "it would only reach 20 feet high."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 714580.0,
      "end_time": 717878.0,
      "text": "And people say it&#39;s poisoning people or doing something --"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 717878.0,
      "end_time": 720801.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s not, it&#39;s just sitting there, it&#39;s just being monitored."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 720801.0,
      "end_time": 722212.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s not very much of it."
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 722212.0,
      "end_time": 726059.0,
      "text": "By contrast, the waste that we don&#39;t control from energy production --"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 726059.0,
      "end_time": 729207.0,
      "text": "we call it &quot;pollution,&quot; and it kills seven million people a year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 729207.0,
      "end_time": 732060.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s threatening very serious levels of global warming."
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 732060.0,
      "end_time": 736036.0,
      "text": "And the truth is that even if we get good at using that waste as fuel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 736036.0,
      "end_time": 738335.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s always going to be some fuel left over."
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 738335.0,
      "end_time": 742230.0,
      "text": "That means there&#39;s always going to be people that think it&#39;s a big problem"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 742230.0,
      "end_time": 745558.0,
      "text": "for reasons that maybe don&#39;t have as much to do with the actual waste"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 745558.0,
      "end_time": 746851.0,
      "text": "as we think."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 746851.0,
      "end_time": 749052.0,
      "text": "Well, what about the weapons?"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 749052.0,
      "end_time": 752369.0,
      "text": "Maybe the most surprising thing is that we can&#39;t find any examples"
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 752369.0,
      "end_time": 754346.0,
      "text": "of countries that have nuclear power"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 754346.0,
      "end_time": 756798.0,
      "text": "and then, &quot;Oh!&quot; decide to go get a weapon."
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 756798.0,
      "end_time": 758524.0,
      "text": "In fact, it works the opposite."
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 758524.0,
      "end_time": 760714.0,
      "text": "What we find is the only way we know"
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 760714.0,
      "end_time": 763190.0,
      "text": "how to get rid large numbers of nuclear weapons"
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 763190.0,
      "end_time": 766014.0,
      "text": "is by using the plutonium in the warheads"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 766014.0,
      "end_time": 768490.0,
      "text": "as fuel in our nuclear power plants."
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 768490.0,
      "end_time": 772428.0,
      "text": "And so, if you are wanting to get the world rid of nuclear weapons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 772428.0,
      "end_time": 775955.0,
      "text": "then we&#39;re going to need a lot more nuclear power."
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 775955.0,
      "end_time": 781515.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 781515.0,
      "end_time": 782905.0,
      "text": "As I was leaving China,"
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 782905.0,
      "end_time": 786118.0,
      "text": "the engineer that brought Bill Gates there kind of pulled me aside,"
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 786118.0,
      "end_time": 788923.0,
      "text": "and he said, &quot;You know, Michael, I appreciate your interest"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 788923.0,
      "end_time": 791654.0,
      "text": "in all the different nuclear supply technologies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 791654.0,
      "end_time": 794600.0,
      "text": "but there&#39;s this more basic issue,"
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 794600.0,
      "end_time": 797163.0,
      "text": "which is that there&#39;s just not enough global demand."
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 797163.0,
      "end_time": 800112.0,
      "text": "I mean, we can crank out these machines on assembly lines,"
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 800112.0,
      "end_time": 801880.0,
      "text": "we do know how to make things cheap,"
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 801880.0,
      "end_time": 804302.0,
      "text": "but there&#39;s just not enough people that want them.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 804302.0,
      "end_time": 809268.0,
      "text": "And so, let&#39;s do solar and wind and efficiency and conservation."
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 809268.0,
      "end_time": 811576.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s accelerate the advanced nuclear programs."
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 811576.0,
      "end_time": 815054.0,
      "text": "I think we should triple the amount of money we&#39;re spending on it."
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 815054.0,
      "end_time": 817467.0,
      "text": "But I just think the most important thing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 817467.0,
      "end_time": 819647.0,
      "text": "if we&#39;re going to overcome the climate crisis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 819647.0,
      "end_time": 824922.0,
      "text": "is to keep in mind that the cause of the clean energy crisis"
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 824922.0,
      "end_time": 827205.0,
      "text": "isn&#39;t from within our machines,"
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 827205.0,
      "end_time": 829557.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s from within ourselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 829557.0,
      "end_time": 830832.0,
      "text": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 830832.0,
      "end_time": 840832.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}